Consistency is the most powerful attribute a human can possess. I’ll give you 5 tips to implement it in your life, but you first must understand that 1% compounding over 365 will revolutionize your life. 

After 10 years of consistency, I have built a body, mindset, and lifestyle that I can proudly promote millions. It’s starts with a goal, builds into education, and results in the actions taken on a daily basis. 

If you’re new to it, here are 5 tips that can get you started: 
1. Set a nightly routine under 15min
2. Incorporate minimum 30min of movement
3. Increase your daily PROTEIN intake
4. Reduce Consumption of Processed Foods
5. Walk 10k Steps per Day

Been documenting this journey for 5 years now and the biggest takeaway is this: 

1. Consistency beats all metrics. 
2. It’s not genetics… it’s mindset. 
3. The reward isn’t at the end, it’s during the journey. 

Now 23 years old and looking to expand from my self and my own personal gain. I’m here to help you achieve the same results I got.

Health is a broad term. We use it to describe a lot of things, but in reality the truth is in the details. 

Here’s what I believe is the most important aspects to your health: 

1. Nutrition including Whole Foods and limiting processed foods. 
2. Movement throughout the day either by walking, exercising, lifting weights, or using the stairs instead of the elevator. 
3. A clear mind through knowledge gained from books or education, tactics like meditation to clear the fog in your head, and reducing the amount of inputs you receive in your head from external influences. 

But curious what you guys think… what do you think is healthy?

The work you do today does not give you the results you see tomorrow. 

There is years of effort and sacrifice that is required to reach the goals that you have. But you don’t have to make it hard. Here’s a few simple suggestions that I give my clients to ensure that they see success without sacrificing their entire life:

1. Find a accountability partner that you can start your journey with. 
2. Surround yourself with people who you aspire to be like (in person and online) 
3. Don’t be afraid to ask questions. 
4. Try something different, because what you have been doing clearly isn’t working the way you want it to. 
5. Continue to grow and improve on your failures instead of dwelling in them.

What’s your story? 

Mine probably isn’t much different than yours. I grew up in a small town, middle class, with a loving family. 

We went through some good times and bad times. 

What I realized is that it doesn’t matter. Your past is just that… your past. 

Who you are today and who you want to be tomorrow is what counts. 

Take 10 minutes today RIGHT BEFORE BED to write short biography of your life after you pass. 

How will people remember you in the year 2082? What are your accomplishments? What kind of person were you?

📸: @damianuslamont
